1
00:00:30,322 --> 00:00:33,951
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

2
00:00:44,044 --> 00:00:46,879
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION
SOME SCENES WERE GENERATED USING AI

3
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:48,966
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

4
00:00:52,261 --> 00:00:54,012
Can I ask you something?

5
00:00:55,597 --> 00:00:56,598
Mm-hmm.

6
00:00:58,058 --> 00:00:59,393
Why did you go to Madeokdo…

7
00:01:00,936 --> 00:01:04,147
with Dr. Hyeon Chiyeon?

8
00:01:06,191 --> 00:01:08,235
We were supposed to go together.

9
00:01:09,486 --> 00:01:10,487
Ah…

10
00:01:11,363 --> 00:01:13,739
How could I have gone there with you?

11
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:15,158
It's not within walking distance.

12
00:01:16,618 --> 00:01:19,121
It's over an hour away by boat.

13
00:01:21,039 --> 00:01:22,124
Ah…

14
00:01:25,627 --> 00:01:27,754
So you were looking out for me.

15
00:01:29,298 --> 00:01:30,424
I didn't even realize that.

16
00:01:34,428 --> 00:01:36,471
But I kind of regret it.

17
00:01:40,434 --> 00:01:42,561
Maybe I shouldn't have looked out for you…

18
00:01:44,146 --> 00:01:46,106
and just gone there with you.

19
00:01:54,406 --> 00:01:55,407
Next time…

20
00:01:57,326 --> 00:01:58,827
do you want to go with me?

21
00:02:02,998 --> 00:02:04,415
Hmm?

22
00:02:09,254 --> 00:02:10,255
Oh…

23
00:02:11,006 --> 00:02:12,549
Rain…

24
00:02:13,508 --> 00:02:16,385
What are you doing? Run!

25
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:31,276
Wow, it's really pouring.

26
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:35,739
Watch your step.

27
00:02:40,243 --> 00:02:41,828
-  Are you okay?
-  Yes.

28
00:02:42,496 --> 00:02:44,497
Which way? Left or right?

29
00:02:44,498 --> 00:02:46,707
-  Right. No, left!
-  Left?

30
00:03:42,139 --> 00:03:44,223
Stop. Let's take a quick breather.

31
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:45,307
Okay.

32
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:08,164
Shall we get going?

33
00:04:08,165 --> 00:04:09,166
Right now?

34
00:04:11,168 --> 00:04:13,878
- Should I go first?
- How about on three?

35
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:15,671
One, two…

36
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:26,892
EPISODE 4 - A NOTORIOUS WOMAN,
A PATHETIC MAN
:cue

37
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:35,775
Dr. Do.

38
00:04:35,776 --> 00:04:37,986
- Hi.
- You're soaking wet.

39
00:04:38,695 --> 00:04:40,738
Ah…

40
00:04:40,739 --> 00:04:41,740
Yes.

41
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:43,574
This is nice.

42
00:04:43,575 --> 00:04:44,576
Yeah.

43
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:47,912
Dr. Do.

44
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,417
Yes?

45
00:04:53,418 --> 00:04:56,296
- Oh, it's nothing.
- Okay.

46
00:05:36,211 --> 00:05:37,878
DID YOU GET HOME SAFELY?

47
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:39,297
PHOTOS

48
00:05:42,884 --> 00:05:46,388
I took a photo of you.
It came out nice.

49
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:53,895
BATHROOM

50
00:06:06,491 --> 00:06:07,868
MS. YUK HARI

51
00:06:16,418 --> 00:06:21,590
WOW, THE FIREFLIES REALLY…

52
00:06:33,476 --> 00:06:34,602
Are you okay?

53
00:06:34,603 --> 00:06:35,811
Yes.

54
00:06:35,812 --> 00:06:37,689
Did you catch a cold because of the rain?

55
00:06:38,899 --> 00:06:42,652
The rain makes the humidity go up.
It's just allergies.

56
00:06:43,737 --> 00:06:45,071
It's only in the morning.

57
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:47,616
Oh… Ah!

58
00:06:48,575 --> 00:06:51,620
About the photos
I took yesterday…

59
00:06:54,039 --> 00:06:55,539
Here's another good one.

60
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:56,790
Did you do all this?

61
00:06:56,791 --> 00:07:01,086
I shaved your jawline and gave you
a nose job. Doesn't it look great?

62
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:02,171
It does.

63
00:07:02,172 --> 00:07:06,551
I got the fireflies and a flattering shot
of your face too.

64
00:07:10,180 --> 00:07:11,680
What the…

65
00:07:11,681 --> 00:07:13,932
This is driving me crazy. I'm so sorry.

66
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:17,102
How can a doctor be so bad
at holding in a sneeze?

67
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:20,189
How are we supposed to hold in a sneeze?
Doctors are human too.

68
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:21,523
Huh?

69
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:24,110
Didn't they teach you how in med school?

70
00:07:24,611 --> 00:07:26,320
There's no such thing.

71
00:07:26,321 --> 00:07:28,782
Oh… I guess they don't teach you.

72
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:32,034
All nurses learn how to do it.

73
00:07:32,035 --> 00:07:35,747
We can't sneeze while we're looking
for a vein or we're in the OR.

74
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:40,292
You're just pulling my leg.

75
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:44,255
I mean it. Have you ever seen
a nurse sneeze in a hospital before?

76
00:07:49,969 --> 00:07:51,221
Want me to tell you how?

77
00:07:53,765 --> 00:07:54,849
Mm-hmm.

78
00:07:56,434 --> 00:07:58,395
Okay. Follow my lead.

79
00:07:59,062 --> 00:08:02,941
First, press your tongue
against the roof of your mouth.

80
00:08:03,942 --> 00:08:06,610
No, further back in.

81
00:08:06,611 --> 00:08:10,948
Next, close your mouth.

82
00:08:10,949 --> 00:08:12,282
That's it.

83
00:08:12,283 --> 00:08:15,870
Now, it's crucial
that you really flare your nostrils.

84
00:08:16,955 --> 00:08:18,580
For proper circulation.

85
00:08:18,581 --> 00:08:20,457
No. Flare it more.

86
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:23,211
Just a little more…

87
00:08:28,758 --> 00:08:31,093
What kind of doctor
falls for such nonsense?

88
00:08:31,094 --> 00:08:33,262
I didn't fall for it.

89
00:08:33,263 --> 00:08:35,473
As if anyone would.

90
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:40,186
Hello?

91
00:08:42,981 --> 00:08:44,691
Okay, I'll head over right away.

92
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:47,317
Okay.

93
00:08:47,318 --> 00:08:49,029
- Did something happen?
- Oh…

94
00:08:49,821 --> 00:08:51,572
Someone requested a home visit.

95
00:08:51,573 --> 00:08:54,492
Someone called your personal phone
to request a home visit?

96
00:08:55,118 --> 00:08:58,287
Uh, yes. They're rather indisposed.

97
00:08:58,288 --> 00:08:59,372
I'll be right back.
:cue

98
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:11,384
Ma'am.

99
00:09:12,385 --> 00:09:14,470
- Are you okay?
- Oh, gosh.

100
00:09:14,471 --> 00:09:17,766
I'm sorry to call you
out of the blue like that.

101
00:09:18,725 --> 00:09:21,018
That's all right.
Let me take a look at your wound.

102
00:09:22,145 --> 00:09:24,605
I came out of my room to take my meds

103
00:09:24,606 --> 00:09:28,359
but I suddenly got dizzy
and just collapsed.

104
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:32,071
Fortunately, it doesn't look deep.
Let me take a look.

105
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:39,204
- Would you take a seat here for me?
- Okay.

106
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,081
Nice and easy.

107
00:09:58,348 --> 00:10:00,350
- It hurts, doesn't it?
- Yes.

108
00:10:08,566 --> 00:10:11,361
CHAVOXIFEN

109
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:14,739
Goodness.

110
00:10:15,406 --> 00:10:17,282
Silly me.

111
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:19,744
I left this out in the open.

112
00:10:22,497 --> 00:10:25,041
I'm guessing those meds are for you.

113
00:10:25,917 --> 00:10:26,918
What?

114
00:10:28,628 --> 00:10:29,712
Yes.

115
00:10:30,505 --> 00:10:32,382
I'm a little unwell.

116
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:34,843
Hmm…

117
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:43,226
Taking painkillers day and night

118
00:10:43,726 --> 00:10:47,062
makes my stomach turn.

119
00:10:47,063 --> 00:10:49,898
So I stopped taking them,
you see.

120
00:10:49,899 --> 00:10:52,277
And look where that's gotten me.

121
00:10:53,278 --> 00:10:56,947
Human bodies can be so miserable.

122
00:10:56,948 --> 00:10:59,491
Don't you think so?

123
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:01,286
Please be sure to take them.

124
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:04,788
Painkillers are a necessary prescription
for a patient.

125
00:11:04,789 --> 00:11:06,165
Okay.

126
00:11:06,166 --> 00:11:09,877
They may not cure your disease,
but they'll let you forget for a moment.

127
00:11:09,878 --> 00:11:11,254
Right.

128
00:11:12,881 --> 00:11:16,634
You should probably
adjust your prescription with your doctor.

129
00:11:17,135 --> 00:11:19,887
I'll check at the center
for any meds that might help.

130
00:11:19,888 --> 00:11:22,557
Oh, no. Don't do that.

131
00:11:23,057 --> 00:11:24,976
I don't want people to find out.

132
00:11:25,894 --> 00:11:29,439
If people were to find out,
they'd all treat me like a sick patient.

133
00:11:30,148 --> 00:11:34,818
I want to live as Hari's grandma, Oh Mija,

134
00:11:34,819 --> 00:11:35,904
not a patient.

135
00:11:37,322 --> 00:11:41,618
The reason I told you to come here
without letting Hari know

136
00:11:42,994 --> 00:11:48,208
was because she makes such a fuss
if I say I'm sick or hurting anywhere.

137
00:11:54,464 --> 00:11:56,173
Don't worry about that.

138
00:11:56,174 --> 00:12:00,636
Doctors have an obligation
to respect their patients' secrets.

139
00:12:02,639 --> 00:12:03,890
But did you know this?

140
00:12:06,017 --> 00:12:10,480
Patients also have an obligation to be
entirely forthcoming to their doctors.

141
00:12:12,690 --> 00:12:14,943
That's why you can tell me everything.

142
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:18,071
:cue

143
00:12:18,947 --> 00:12:19,948
Yes.

144
00:12:20,657 --> 00:12:22,824
I understand, Doctor.

145
00:12:22,825 --> 00:12:24,160
Right.

146
00:12:34,003 --> 00:12:35,462
Ms. Yuk.

147
00:12:35,463 --> 00:12:37,757
My grandma was the urgent patient?

148
00:12:39,425 --> 00:12:41,343
Is my grandma okay? I'm going in.

149
00:12:41,344 --> 00:12:42,345
Wait.

150
00:12:43,137 --> 00:12:45,931
I don't think you should go in just yet.

151
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:58,444
I guess my grandma finds
the doctor she met once

152
00:12:59,112 --> 00:13:01,906
to be more reliable
than her own granddaughter.

153
00:13:03,866 --> 00:13:06,159
Then again, if I were her,

154
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:10,081
I wouldn't have told me either.

155
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:13,876
Because I'd cry more than my sick grandma.

156
00:13:20,341 --> 00:13:23,177
And I keep trying to forget
that she is sick.

157
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:28,057
Thinking about it is too scary.

158
00:13:32,979 --> 00:13:34,230
I'm a coward, aren't I?

159
00:13:38,109 --> 00:13:39,193
No.

160
00:13:45,199 --> 00:13:48,703
To be honest, when I first met you…

161
00:13:50,705 --> 00:13:51,998
I saw it in your suitcase.

162
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,084
The anti-cancer drug…

163
00:13:56,961 --> 00:13:58,171
Chavoxifen.

164
00:14:00,006 --> 00:14:01,049
Mmm…

165
00:14:03,634 --> 00:14:06,137
At first, I thought you
were the one who was sick.

166
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:11,642
But I couldn't bring myself
to ask you about it.

167
00:14:13,352 --> 00:14:15,438
Even if I knew how much you were hurting…

168
00:14:17,648 --> 00:14:20,109
it's not like
I could have done anything about it.

169
00:14:23,154 --> 00:14:24,155
And…

170
00:14:26,074 --> 00:14:27,283
it was scary.

171
00:14:29,911 --> 00:14:31,996
I'm sure it's not even close…

172
00:14:33,998 --> 00:14:35,249
…but I'm saying…

173
00:14:36,876 --> 00:14:38,920
I kind of get how you feel.

174
00:14:42,465 --> 00:14:44,050
You're not a coward.

175
00:14:46,344 --> 00:14:48,137
Anyone would feel that way.

176
00:15:06,489 --> 00:15:07,824
Ah…

177
00:15:10,785 --> 00:15:12,537
I think we've been away for too long.

178
00:15:13,121 --> 00:15:14,621
Ah…

179
00:15:14,622 --> 00:15:15,623
Shall we go?

180
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:18,668
Uh, sure.
:cue

181
00:15:33,766 --> 00:15:37,520
Mom,
why did you send so many side dishes?

182
00:15:38,104 --> 00:15:39,771
I can't finish all this on my own.

183
00:15:39,772 --> 00:15:41,898
I packed enough to share with everyone.

184
00:15:41,899 --> 00:15:46,194
You said the people there like you so much
that the place couldn't run without you.

185
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:48,322
Okay. Bye.

186
00:15:50,074 --> 00:15:51,826
Goodness.

187
00:15:56,914 --> 00:15:58,166
What's gotten into him now?

188
00:16:03,296 --> 00:16:04,546
Sorry for stepping away.

189
00:16:04,547 --> 00:16:07,091
It's fine.
We didn't get that many patients.

190
00:16:08,551 --> 00:16:09,926
Dr. Do.

191
00:16:09,927 --> 00:16:11,469
We need to talk.

192
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:13,306
- What for?
- Hurry…

193
00:16:18,311 --> 00:16:19,312
What…

194
00:16:20,605 --> 00:16:21,856
What is it?

195
00:16:24,317 --> 00:16:25,984
This just isn't right.

196
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:27,194
What's this about?

197
00:16:27,195 --> 00:16:29,197
You haven't seen the PH doc group chat?

198
00:16:30,573 --> 00:16:32,241
They talk so much, so…

199
00:16:33,743 --> 00:16:35,368
Is something wrong?

200
00:16:35,369 --> 00:16:38,496
I'm not comfortable saying it myself,
so just check it out now.

201
00:16:38,497 --> 00:16:39,707
Come on!

202
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:41,250
Okay.

203
00:16:45,254 --> 00:16:48,298
JEONNAM PH DOC GROUP CHAT

204
00:16:48,299 --> 00:16:49,758
Stop everything. Major PSA.

205
00:16:49,759 --> 00:16:52,135
Has a nurse recently joined
any of your health centers?

206
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:54,554
Apparently, she's notorious
for being a doctor hunter.

207
00:16:54,555 --> 00:16:57,557
I heard she only goes after
doctors. Could she be doing it here too?

208
00:16:57,558 --> 00:17:01,187
It looks like they're talking
about Ms. Yuk Hari, doesn't it?

209
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:03,188
Not at all.

210
00:17:03,189 --> 00:17:06,024
Who else but Ms. Yuk
could have transferred from Asong Hospital

211
00:17:06,025 --> 00:17:08,652
to an island as a contract nurse?

212
00:17:08,653 --> 00:17:12,615
And I got all my friends at Asong Hospital
to do some digging for me.

213
00:17:13,616 --> 00:17:15,409
Guess how many doctors Ms. Yuk got to.

214
00:17:17,036 --> 00:17:18,371
Three.

215
00:17:19,538 --> 00:17:21,082
T-Three?

216
00:17:24,585 --> 00:17:26,087
Be honest with me.

217
00:17:28,005 --> 00:17:30,048
You've also felt it, haven't you?

218
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:33,135
How Ms. Yuk has gotten her hooks in.

219
00:17:34,679 --> 00:17:36,429
Whoa, I'm not…

220
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:38,890
She hasn't gotten her hooks in
or anything like that.

221
00:17:38,891 --> 00:17:40,226
I'm telling you,

222
00:17:40,726 --> 00:17:43,270
she's definitely gotten her hooks in!

223
00:17:43,271 --> 00:17:44,814
Into Dr. Hyeon Chiyeon!

224
00:17:46,774 --> 00:17:47,857
What?

225
00:17:47,858 --> 00:17:51,320
Everyone knew
those two were going out except us!

226
00:17:52,154 --> 00:17:58,660
So you're saying Dr. Hyeon Chiyeon is
going out with Ms. Yuk Hari, huh?

227
00:17:58,661 --> 00:18:00,036
I saw it myself.

228
00:18:00,037 --> 00:18:02,373
They were riding around
on an ATV together.

229
00:18:08,546 --> 00:18:12,048
If they shared an ATV ride,
they're practically an item, no?

230
00:18:12,049 --> 00:18:13,759
Practically an item indeed.

231
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:19,265
Oh, my.

232
00:18:20,474 --> 00:18:21,767
Gosh.

233
00:18:22,351 --> 00:18:24,478
To be so young and in love again.

234
00:18:26,814 --> 00:18:29,274
You know what the chief of Madeokdo said?

235
00:18:29,275 --> 00:18:31,736
He said sparks were flying
between those two.

236
00:18:32,236 --> 00:18:34,988
And I heard there was only
one available room that night.

237
00:18:34,989 --> 00:18:37,574
No wonder you could see hearts
in their eyes.

238
00:18:37,575 --> 00:18:38,992
Hearts in their eyes?

239
00:18:38,993 --> 00:18:42,204
Looks like we might be having
a wedding on Pyeondongdo!

240
00:18:43,331 --> 00:18:46,249
The ATV was because
Dr. Hyeon came to pick us up.

241
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:48,251
And Madeokdo was because
they missed the boat.

242
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:50,671
So let's not talk
behind our coworkers' backs, okay?

243
00:18:52,423 --> 00:18:54,008
- Wow.
- So not cool.

244
00:18:59,722 --> 00:19:02,932
It's time to head over
to the health education session, right?

245
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:03,934
Yes.

246
00:19:04,602 --> 00:19:07,395
If you use too much
technical jargon to explain,

247
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:09,982
no one will understand,
so when explaining…

248
00:19:13,194 --> 00:19:15,154
Look at me running my mouth.

249
00:19:16,322 --> 00:19:20,034
I'm sure you'll nail it
without any instructions.

250
00:19:21,285 --> 00:19:23,204
We'll be going now.

251
00:19:24,622 --> 00:19:25,706
I'll see you later.

252
00:19:30,044 --> 00:19:32,213
- I'll see you later.
-  Good luck.

253
00:19:48,813 --> 00:19:50,230
I'm good.

254
00:19:50,231 --> 00:19:51,690
- Let me carry it for you.
-  No.

255
00:19:51,691 --> 00:19:55,736
I'm telling you,
she's definitely gotten her hooks in!

256
00:19:56,445 --> 00:19:57,822
Into Dr. Hyeon Chiyeon!

257
00:20:12,753 --> 00:20:14,088
Ms. Hwang.

258
00:20:15,297 --> 00:20:17,049
Any plans for the evening?

259
00:20:17,550 --> 00:20:22,178
I just figured
we might have dinner together.

260
00:20:22,179 --> 00:20:24,222
What for? Any special occasion?

261
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:25,598
:cue

262
00:20:25,599 --> 00:20:29,562
My mom sent me a buttload of side dishes,
so I thought we could…

263
00:20:30,104 --> 00:20:33,773
Then just bring it over here tomorrow
so we can have it together.

264
00:20:33,774 --> 00:20:36,026
Ah…

265
00:20:38,946 --> 00:20:40,447
- There's a solution.
- Right.

266
00:20:40,448 --> 00:20:41,949
Why didn't I think of that?

267
00:20:48,748 --> 00:20:51,082
They were supposed to
take that to the session!

268
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:53,001
They left it behind.

269
00:20:53,002 --> 00:20:55,462
How careless. I'll take it to them.

270
00:20:57,548 --> 00:20:58,631
I…

271
00:20:58,632 --> 00:21:00,134
I will go.

272
00:21:00,718 --> 00:21:02,178
Was he listening in on us?

273
00:21:05,347 --> 00:21:06,931
- Village Hall, right?
- Right.

274
00:21:06,932 --> 00:21:07,975
Mmm…

275
00:21:10,686 --> 00:21:12,562
PYEONDONGDO VILLAGE HALL

276
00:21:12,563 --> 00:21:13,646
That's right.

277
00:21:13,647 --> 00:21:17,567
Once you've called emergency services,
you need to check for a response.

278
00:21:17,568 --> 00:21:20,487
Watch me. Take your palms, and say…

279
00:21:20,488 --> 00:21:22,531
"Sir, are you okay?"

280
00:21:23,449 --> 00:21:25,325
He's not responding, right?

281
00:21:25,326 --> 00:21:28,036
In that case,
you have to check if they're breathing.

282
00:21:28,037 --> 00:21:29,746
Place your hand on their chest,

283
00:21:29,747 --> 00:21:31,707
listen for breaths with your ear,

284
00:21:32,625 --> 00:21:36,670
and check to see
whether their chest is rising and falling.

285
00:21:37,588 --> 00:21:39,340
Have you washed your hair?

286
00:21:42,384 --> 00:21:45,429
You have to press down really hard.

287
00:21:45,930 --> 00:21:49,933
So hard that it feels like
the rib cage might collapse!

288
00:21:49,934 --> 00:21:52,560
Oh, man. She brought him back to life!

289
00:21:53,771 --> 00:21:56,439
- He really came back to life.
- Wow, he came back!

290
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:57,565
Are you okay?

291
00:21:57,566 --> 00:22:01,402
You two make a fantastic couple.

292
00:22:01,403 --> 00:22:03,154
I can see you as a married couple.

293
00:22:03,155 --> 00:22:05,448
- I know.
-  And don't you try to deny it.

294
00:22:05,449 --> 00:22:08,368
Even the pebbles have eyes
here in Pyeondongdo.

295
00:22:08,369 --> 00:22:10,620
Come on. It's not like that.

296
00:22:10,621 --> 00:22:11,704
It's not.

297
00:22:11,705 --> 00:22:13,039
What do you mean, no?

298
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:17,085
I heard young people nowadays start off
by taking it slow with a situationship

299
00:22:17,086 --> 00:22:19,587
before they make it official.
That's what it is, right?

300
00:22:19,588 --> 00:22:21,005
It's not…

301
00:22:21,006 --> 00:22:22,799
That's enough.

302
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:25,176
Now, now. Stop teasing us.

303
00:22:25,177 --> 00:22:28,721
We'll move on to hygiene training.
Let's get ready.

304
00:22:28,722 --> 00:22:30,974
-  What? Hygiene training?
-  Oh?

305
00:22:30,975 --> 00:22:34,060
When are you gonna tell us
about the ventilator?

306
00:22:34,061 --> 00:22:35,896
Huh? The ventilator!

307
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:40,441
We came here to check this out.
Remember? The ventilator!

308
00:22:40,442 --> 00:22:41,443
What about this?

309
00:22:43,070 --> 00:22:45,197
I'm done! No more!

310
00:22:50,744 --> 00:22:51,828
Oh…

311
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:12,057
People here come up with
totally baseless rumors.

312
00:23:13,434 --> 00:23:15,852
Why didn't you say anything?

313
00:23:15,853 --> 00:23:18,022
That's like adding fuel to the fire.

314
00:23:18,689 --> 00:23:21,650
I just didn't think
they were totally baseless.

315
00:23:22,359 --> 00:23:23,360
What?

316
00:23:25,070 --> 00:23:26,780
Does it bother you that much?

317
00:23:27,740 --> 00:23:29,491
Rumors can be really powerful.

318
00:23:30,326 --> 00:23:34,079
Once people get swept up by a rumor,
they don't even care about the truth.

319
00:23:35,915 --> 00:23:37,499
That's why I don't like rumors.

320
00:23:38,834 --> 00:23:39,960
I understand.

321
00:23:40,461 --> 00:23:41,545
I'll be careful.

322
00:23:44,506 --> 00:23:46,300
Bokdol. Boksun.

323
00:23:47,009 --> 00:23:48,636
What do you guys think?

324
00:23:49,136 --> 00:23:50,930
Should I tell him?

325
00:23:51,680 --> 00:23:53,390
Or should I not?

326
00:23:54,642 --> 00:23:55,809
Should I?

327
00:23:56,769 --> 00:23:58,062
Or should I not?

328
00:24:00,439 --> 00:24:01,440
Dr. Yong.

329
00:24:01,941 --> 00:24:05,235
The herbs we ordered didn't arrive,
so I'm going to order them again.

330
00:24:07,154 --> 00:24:08,322
Okay.

331
00:24:12,201 --> 00:24:14,662
Did you hear what I said?
About ordering them again?

332
00:24:16,830 --> 00:24:17,831
I did.

333
00:24:19,458 --> 00:24:22,294
What are you doing right now
during consultation hours?

334
00:24:24,004 --> 00:24:27,508
All the elderly have gone to the session,
so we have no patients.

335
00:24:31,762 --> 00:24:33,096
What was that for?

336
00:24:33,097 --> 00:24:35,974
I'm feeding them. Look at them eat.

337
00:24:35,975 --> 00:24:38,143
These guys aren't meant
to be raised like that!

338
00:24:39,019 --> 00:24:40,770
You don't have any friends, do you?

339
00:24:40,771 --> 00:24:43,022
- You have no one to hang out with, right?
- What?

340
00:24:43,023 --> 00:24:44,607
You pick on me all the time

341
00:24:44,608 --> 00:24:47,444
because you're bored
and have no friends, right?

342
00:24:48,028 --> 00:24:49,613
I'm the one picking on you?

343
00:24:50,197 --> 00:24:53,658
I'm wrestling with
a serious dilemma right now, okay?

344
00:24:53,659 --> 00:24:55,994
The prince is in a dilemma, huh?

345
00:24:55,995 --> 00:24:58,454
You're probably just torn between
two luxury choices!

346
00:24:58,455 --> 00:25:00,833
Wrestle away, your highness!

347
00:25:06,755 --> 00:25:09,132
The fate of our center
hangs in the balance!

348
00:25:09,133 --> 00:25:11,176
You have no idea, damn it.

349
00:25:12,052 --> 00:25:15,096
Why'd she have to dump
all that expensive food in there?

350
00:25:15,097 --> 00:25:17,307
I can't even get it out now.
:cue

351
00:25:25,107 --> 00:25:26,232
Dr. Do.

352
00:25:27,401 --> 00:25:28,484
Hi.

353
00:25:28,485 --> 00:25:29,778
Are you here for beer?

354
00:25:30,404 --> 00:25:33,741
That's great. I've been wanting
to grab a beer with you.

355
00:25:34,366 --> 00:25:38,120
Take your pick. Drinks are on me tonight
since I owe you and all.

356
00:25:39,705 --> 00:25:44,168
I don't actually feel
like drinking beer today.

357
00:25:44,877 --> 00:25:45,878
Really?

358
00:25:47,796 --> 00:25:49,338
I didn't know that was possible.

359
00:25:50,883 --> 00:25:53,218
Oh, right.
You came to the village hall today, right?

360
00:25:54,428 --> 00:25:56,388
Yes. You had left something behind.

361
00:25:57,181 --> 00:26:00,516
Why did you just leave?
You could have stayed and helped.

362
00:26:00,517 --> 00:26:03,227
You didn't have many patients today
because of the session.

363
00:26:03,228 --> 00:26:06,231
Well, you seemed to be doing fine
with Dr. Chiyeon.

364
00:26:06,774 --> 00:26:09,651
So I wasn't sure I should butt in.

365
00:26:13,155 --> 00:26:14,490
Dr. Do.

366
00:26:17,159 --> 00:26:19,328
Did I upset you in some way?

367
00:26:22,122 --> 00:26:24,291
No, not at all.

368
00:26:24,875 --> 00:26:25,959
Really?

369
00:26:27,211 --> 00:26:28,420
Guess I'm just imagining it.

370
00:26:31,381 --> 00:26:34,176
Then let's have a beer out by the beach.

371
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:37,012
The breeze is nice,
and we've got plenty of snacks.

372
00:26:37,930 --> 00:26:40,807
No, I don't want people to get
the wrong idea about us.

373
00:26:40,808 --> 00:26:42,643
What do you mean, the wrong idea?

374
00:26:44,269 --> 00:26:45,437
I had no idea

375
00:26:46,146 --> 00:26:48,982
that you and Dr. Chiyeon were, well…

376
00:26:50,192 --> 00:26:52,736
Wait, you also believe those rumors?

377
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:57,324
Come on, that's just the village elders
gossiping among themselves.

378
00:26:58,951 --> 00:27:01,578
It didn't seem to be just a rumor.
The two of you…

379
00:27:04,790 --> 00:27:06,375
seemed really close.

380
00:27:09,753 --> 00:27:14,633
I don't know why I should have to
defend myself about this.

381
00:27:15,717 --> 00:27:18,177
But if being seen as close
starts those rumors,

382
00:27:18,178 --> 00:27:20,221
shouldn't there be more rumors about us?

383
00:27:20,222 --> 00:27:21,931
We spent the night together,

384
00:27:21,932 --> 00:27:24,100
drank together,
and even got caught in the rain.

385
00:27:24,101 --> 00:27:26,435
Doing things like that
with just anyone is why

386
00:27:26,436 --> 00:27:31,233
they're spreading rumors about you being
a doctor hunter and a gold digger.

387
00:27:37,573 --> 00:27:39,241
I mean…

388
00:27:39,867 --> 00:27:40,993
I see.

389
00:27:43,704 --> 00:27:46,456
I thought you were acting
a little strange today…

390
00:27:48,792 --> 00:27:51,211
So you were scared
that I'd get my hooks in?

391
00:27:52,796 --> 00:27:55,006
No, that's not what I mean--

392
00:27:55,007 --> 00:27:56,049
Don't be scared.

393
00:27:57,843 --> 00:27:59,970
I have no intention
of getting my hooks into you.

394
00:28:00,721 --> 00:28:02,306
Ms. Yuk, I didn't mean it like…

395
00:28:10,731 --> 00:28:12,232
You stupid idiot…

396
00:28:21,074 --> 00:28:23,160
Setting timer for one minute.

397
00:28:35,881 --> 00:28:36,882
Dr. Hyeon.

398
00:28:37,466 --> 00:28:38,926
I need to tell you something.

399
00:28:39,426 --> 00:28:41,053
But don't turn around.

400
00:28:41,803 --> 00:28:44,556
I don't think I can tell you
if I looked you in the eye.

401
00:28:45,724 --> 00:28:47,517
I've given it a lot of thought,
:cue

402
00:28:48,101 --> 00:28:50,228
and it feels like
this is the right thing to do.

403
00:28:52,356 --> 00:28:54,857
Listen closely to what I'm about to say.

404
00:28:57,194 --> 00:28:59,071
Ms. Yuk Hari…

405
00:28:59,696 --> 00:29:02,658
She's not going out with you
because she actually likes you.

406
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:04,993
Ms. Yuk Hari is…

407
00:29:07,371 --> 00:29:09,163
a doctor hunter!

408
00:29:09,164 --> 00:29:10,415
Holy crap.

409
00:29:14,419 --> 00:29:16,421
Are you in shock?

410
00:29:17,506 --> 00:29:18,966
Dr. Hyeon?

411
00:29:20,050 --> 00:29:21,051
Yes?

412
00:29:22,552 --> 00:29:23,637
What is it?

413
00:29:25,555 --> 00:29:27,848
Why would you wear those in the quarters?

414
00:29:27,849 --> 00:29:30,393
Did you not hear anything I said just now?

415
00:29:30,394 --> 00:29:31,478
The heck?

416
00:29:38,235 --> 00:29:39,610
Hello?

417
00:29:39,611 --> 00:29:41,278
This is Eom Jeongseon.

418
00:29:41,279 --> 00:29:44,240
I'm in the middle of something important,
so call me again later.

419
00:29:44,241 --> 00:29:46,534
I doubt it's more important than this.

420
00:29:46,535 --> 00:29:49,245
Your phone is with me.

421
00:29:49,246 --> 00:29:52,582
That's nonsense.
I'm literally on the phone right now.

422
00:29:54,459 --> 00:29:55,460
"Ninnyhammer"?

423
00:29:56,837 --> 00:29:59,255
Who the heck is this Ninnyhammer?

424
00:29:59,256 --> 00:30:02,675
- Hello?
- You took my phone, and I took yours!

425
00:30:02,676 --> 00:30:05,012
How did that happen?

426
00:30:08,098 --> 00:30:11,600
How the heck should I know?
Bring it over to me right now!

427
00:30:11,601 --> 00:30:14,145
Me? Why should I?

428
00:30:14,146 --> 00:30:17,064
Oh, my. I guess you don't want
to go on leave anymore.

429
00:30:17,065 --> 00:30:19,108
- What?
- Right now.

430
00:30:25,157 --> 00:30:26,407
Damn it!

431
00:30:29,745 --> 00:30:32,289
Dr. Hyeon, do you know
what "ninnyhammer" means?

432
00:30:33,081 --> 00:30:34,498
Stupid…

433
00:30:34,499 --> 00:30:36,334
- Idiot?
- What?

434
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:40,756
Damn it.

435
00:30:47,054 --> 00:30:49,473
Who does she think she is,
telling me to come over?

436
00:31:09,201 --> 00:31:10,202
Here.

437
00:31:13,997 --> 00:31:16,249
Be more careful from now on.

438
00:31:17,417 --> 00:31:20,212
Look who's talking.
You're the one who took mine.

439
00:31:26,510 --> 00:31:27,511
What the…

440
00:31:28,136 --> 00:31:31,305
What's with the feast?
Throwing a party or something?

441
00:31:31,306 --> 00:31:33,140
What's it to you?

442
00:31:33,141 --> 00:31:35,143
Seaweed soup and ribs.

443
00:31:36,103 --> 00:31:38,062
Is it your birthday or something?

444
00:31:42,651 --> 00:31:43,693
It's your birthday?

445
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:48,073
Who eats by themselves on their birthday?

446
00:31:51,076 --> 00:31:52,701
It's because I have no friends!

447
00:31:52,702 --> 00:31:53,703
Just go!

448
00:32:13,557 --> 00:32:14,850
:cue

449
00:32:19,479 --> 00:32:20,646
What?

450
00:32:20,647 --> 00:32:21,898
I'll be your friend.

451
00:32:22,607 --> 00:32:24,067
What?

452
00:32:24,818 --> 00:32:25,819
What…

453
00:32:26,319 --> 00:32:27,737
What are you doing?

454
00:32:30,490 --> 00:32:31,907
Oh…

455
00:32:31,908 --> 00:32:33,033
It looks so good.

456
00:32:33,034 --> 00:32:34,952
Grab yourself a bowl of rice and sit.

457
00:32:34,953 --> 00:32:38,373
I asked you what you're doing!

458
00:32:41,334 --> 00:32:42,544
Ah…

459
00:32:45,213 --> 00:32:47,173
Isn't it obvious?

460
00:32:47,174 --> 00:32:49,300
I'm throwing you a birthday party.

461
00:32:49,301 --> 00:32:51,386
Who eats by themselves on their birthday?

462
00:32:52,596 --> 00:32:55,765
And just so you know,
there are three essentials for a birthday.

463
00:32:56,266 --> 00:33:00,103
A birthday feast, friends,
and birthday drinks.

464
00:33:00,812 --> 00:33:02,354
Do you have any alcohol?

465
00:33:13,575 --> 00:33:15,327
Okay.

466
00:33:16,036 --> 00:33:17,870
One, two, three, four.

467
00:33:17,871 --> 00:33:23,167
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

468
00:33:23,168 --> 00:33:24,169
♪ Happy birthday, de… ♪

469
00:33:26,296 --> 00:33:28,297
♪ Ms. Jeongseon ♪

470
00:33:28,298 --> 00:33:30,257
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

471
00:33:32,093 --> 00:33:33,094
Blow them out.

472
00:33:39,309 --> 00:33:42,187
You're taking a lot of credit
for a feast you didn't even prepare.

473
00:33:43,647 --> 00:33:44,940
Happy birthday.

474
00:33:45,565 --> 00:33:48,108
Oh, hold on,

475
00:33:48,109 --> 00:33:49,569
I prepared something for you.

476
00:33:55,325 --> 00:33:56,409
Ta-da!

477
00:34:06,753 --> 00:34:07,962
Shall we toast?

478
00:34:07,963 --> 00:34:09,171
I'm sorry.

479
00:34:11,633 --> 00:34:12,634
Cheers.

480
00:34:22,185 --> 00:34:24,770
I wasn't expecting
a prince like you to care so much

481
00:34:24,771 --> 00:34:27,440
- about someone else's birthday.
- Hmm.

482
00:34:28,525 --> 00:34:34,280
I've always thought that birthdays
should be lively, joyous occasions.

483
00:34:34,281 --> 00:34:36,323
Of course you did.

484
00:34:36,324 --> 00:34:39,077
Not that I ever got to enjoy that.

485
00:34:42,747 --> 00:34:44,081
Ah.

486
00:34:44,082 --> 00:34:50,380
The truth is that I kind of got picked on.

487
00:34:53,174 --> 00:34:56,219
The son of a Korean Medicine clinic
director in Seoul got picked on?

488
00:34:57,929 --> 00:34:58,930
I know, right?

489
00:34:59,598 --> 00:35:01,015
Isn't that really weird?

490
00:35:01,016 --> 00:35:04,351
I don't get why someone
would hate on a kid from a rich family

491
00:35:04,352 --> 00:35:06,855
who's as adorable and nice as me.

492
00:35:11,067 --> 00:35:15,905
That's why I'm not a huge fan of
people spending birthdays alone.

493
00:35:20,535 --> 00:35:24,331
So you won't be
spending it by yourself today.

494
00:35:24,831 --> 00:35:26,416
You'll be spending it with me.

495
00:35:33,131 --> 00:35:34,215
Cheers!
:cue

496
00:36:11,211 --> 00:36:12,336
MS. YUK HARI

497
00:36:17,217 --> 00:36:18,300
Hello?

498
00:36:18,301 --> 00:36:21,428
Dr. Do,
please come to the center right now.

499
00:36:21,429 --> 00:36:23,098
- Hurry.
- Huh?

500
00:36:29,854 --> 00:36:31,981
Okay. Let's apologize to her in person.

501
00:36:34,609 --> 00:36:36,069
Hmm?

502
00:36:37,153 --> 00:36:38,404
Dr. Do.

503
00:36:38,405 --> 00:36:39,406
What is it?

504
00:36:42,826 --> 00:36:43,952
Hold on…

505
00:36:45,912 --> 00:36:48,622
That's a fishhook. How did this happen?

506
00:36:48,623 --> 00:36:50,375
During a meal, apparently.

507
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:53,002
I guess the fish still had a hook in it.

508
00:36:53,753 --> 00:36:55,587
- The lidocaine, please.
- Okay.

509
00:36:55,588 --> 00:36:58,632
- You've gotten your tetanus shot, right?
- Uh-huh, uh-huh, uh-huh.

510
00:36:58,633 --> 00:37:00,218
I'll remove it in no time.

511
00:37:02,804 --> 00:37:04,304
This is going to sting.

512
00:37:09,352 --> 00:37:10,519
What happened?

513
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:12,105
He got a hook stuck in his tongue.

514
00:37:14,107 --> 00:37:15,692
Hold on.

515
00:37:16,276 --> 00:37:18,194
Fishhooks aren't like regular needles.

516
00:37:18,820 --> 00:37:20,863
They have a barb at the tip,

517
00:37:20,864 --> 00:37:23,031
so just pulling it
could tear the tissue apart.

518
00:37:23,032 --> 00:37:25,618
That'll cause way more damage.

519
00:37:26,286 --> 00:37:27,662
Then what should we do?

520
00:37:30,331 --> 00:37:32,167
I've done it before, so I'll do it.

521
00:37:37,964 --> 00:37:40,175
- Have you administered lidocaine?
-  Yes.

522
00:37:44,429 --> 00:37:46,890
Can you feel this?

523
00:38:08,787 --> 00:38:10,287
Okay, we're done.

524
00:38:13,041 --> 00:38:14,958
Thank you so much. Ow.

525
00:38:14,959 --> 00:38:16,418
I'll prescribe some antibiotics,

526
00:38:16,419 --> 00:38:18,295
so be sure to take them.

527
00:38:18,296 --> 00:38:20,964
I'll help you with
the rest outside. Watch your step.

528
00:38:20,965 --> 00:38:22,257
You can head on up now.

529
00:38:22,258 --> 00:38:24,676
I'm on call,
so I'll write the prescription.

530
00:38:24,677 --> 00:38:25,678
Okay.

531
00:38:56,125 --> 00:38:57,752
Man, my head is killing me.

532
00:39:27,240 --> 00:39:28,241
What the…

533
00:39:30,410 --> 00:39:31,744
What the heck?

534
00:39:34,080 --> 00:39:36,749
No way.

535
00:39:37,250 --> 00:39:40,044
:cue

536
00:39:47,260 --> 00:39:48,511
Why don't you get up now?

537
00:39:53,266 --> 00:39:54,766
I know you're awake, so get up!

538
00:39:54,767 --> 00:39:56,603
I can see you in the mirror!

539
00:40:03,693 --> 00:40:04,986
I'm sorry.

540
00:40:06,696 --> 00:40:08,740
- What?
- I'm…

541
00:40:09,991 --> 00:40:14,411
I'm not sure how this happened,
but I'm really sorry.

542
00:40:18,708 --> 00:40:22,753
Well, whether you remember it or not,

543
00:40:22,754 --> 00:40:24,796
or whether you're pretending
not to remember,

544
00:40:24,797 --> 00:40:27,716
I couldn't care less,
so just do what you will.

545
00:40:27,717 --> 00:40:32,221
What really matters to me right now is
that no one sees you leaving my house.

546
00:40:33,097 --> 00:40:35,307
If someone saw you sneaking out of here,

547
00:40:35,308 --> 00:40:38,101
can you imagine
the scandal that would cause?

548
00:40:38,102 --> 00:40:39,646
That's right.

549
00:40:40,355 --> 00:40:42,522
Which is why I'm going to leave right now,

550
00:40:42,523 --> 00:40:45,067
and you should wait 20 minutes
before you leave.

551
00:40:45,068 --> 00:40:48,278
That's when the grannies gather
at the village hall to play Go-Stop.

552
00:40:48,279 --> 00:40:49,572
Mmm.

553
00:40:51,074 --> 00:40:53,241
Let the center know you'll be late, okay?

554
00:40:53,242 --> 00:40:56,078
Y-Yes. I-I'll call them. Okay.

555
00:41:04,379 --> 00:41:05,797
And about last night…

556
00:41:08,091 --> 00:41:09,133
Last night…

557
00:41:11,052 --> 00:41:13,513
Let's just forget it ever happened.

558
00:41:16,265 --> 00:41:18,141
Stick to the plan. Twenty minutes!

559
00:41:18,142 --> 00:41:19,435
Right. Twenty minutes.

560
00:41:28,236 --> 00:41:29,570
I'm so screwed.

561
00:41:33,908 --> 00:41:34,909
Damn it.

562
00:41:42,083 --> 00:41:43,084
Damn it.

563
00:41:47,046 --> 00:41:48,338
Oh, Dr. Yong!

564
00:41:48,339 --> 00:41:50,466
- I just cleaned that area!
- Oh, I'm sorry.

565
00:41:51,050 --> 00:41:52,968
Why did you enter through that door?

566
00:41:52,969 --> 00:41:54,012
Sorry?

567
00:41:54,637 --> 00:41:55,638
Well, I…

568
00:41:57,265 --> 00:41:59,057
I was out on a walk.

569
00:41:59,058 --> 00:42:03,020
Oh, you're late to work
because you were exercising?

570
00:42:03,021 --> 00:42:04,479
How admirable.

571
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:05,940
Thank you.

572
00:42:08,568 --> 00:42:11,863
Mmm. Give it to me.

573
00:42:14,615 --> 00:42:17,618
Hello? This is the Public Health Center.

574
00:42:19,203 --> 00:42:22,164
Huh? What?

575
00:42:22,165 --> 00:42:24,791
But why would
someone like that come here…

576
00:42:26,127 --> 00:42:27,335
Mmm.

577
00:42:27,336 --> 00:42:29,505
Yes, I understand.

578
00:42:31,716 --> 00:42:34,635
- Hang up. Hang up.
- Ms. Hwang, are you okay?

579
00:42:35,344 --> 00:42:37,804
Goodness me, what a disaster.

580
00:42:37,805 --> 00:42:39,057
What is it? What happened?

581
00:42:40,058 --> 00:42:44,687
Choi Hyangmi, the Director of
Public Health Care Services,

582
00:42:45,313 --> 00:42:48,315
is coming to our center right now
to give us an official warning.

583
00:42:48,316 --> 00:42:50,735
Choi Hyangmi is coming in person
to our center?

584
00:42:51,319 --> 00:42:52,737
What's an official warning?

585
00:42:55,740 --> 00:42:59,326
An official warning is
a penalty that applies to civil servants,

586
00:42:59,327 --> 00:43:00,869
and it can accumulate.

587
00:43:00,870 --> 00:43:05,165
If a PH doc gets too many warnings,
they can dock your pay,

588
00:43:05,166 --> 00:43:07,918
restrict your leave,
and in the worst-case scenario,

589
00:43:07,919 --> 00:43:10,045
even extend your mandatory service.

590
00:43:10,046 --> 00:43:12,298
Horrifying, if you ask me.

591
00:43:15,718 --> 00:43:16,886
Yes, governor.

592
00:43:18,554 --> 00:43:21,224
It's a little windy,
but the ferry has departed.

593
00:43:22,642 --> 00:43:24,310
I'll report to you once I return.

594
00:43:25,728 --> 00:43:26,771
Okay.
:cue

595
00:43:35,279 --> 00:43:36,405
Who was it?

596
00:43:36,948 --> 00:43:40,159
Did any of you slip up
while I wasn't looking?

597
00:43:40,952 --> 00:43:41,953
Huh?

598
00:43:42,912 --> 00:43:43,996
Uh…

599
00:43:45,206 --> 00:43:46,207
By any chance…

600
00:43:48,167 --> 00:43:52,088
ca-ca-can one's private life or…
…rumors…

601
00:43:53,297 --> 00:43:56,049
- be the cause of--
- Why would you bring that up now? Sheesh.

602
00:43:56,050 --> 00:43:59,219
Calm down! Everyone, wear your gowns!

603
00:43:59,220 --> 00:44:00,804
Get changed, pronto!

604
00:44:00,805 --> 00:44:02,639
Wear your civil servant IDs.

605
00:44:02,640 --> 00:44:04,141
- Ms. Hwang. Ms. Hwang.
- What is it?

606
00:44:04,142 --> 00:44:07,227
I'm sorry, but I haven't received
my civil servant ID yet.

607
00:44:07,228 --> 00:44:09,522
- I have applied for one, though.
-  What?

608
00:44:10,189 --> 00:44:12,525
Why are you
telling me this now?

609
00:44:13,234 --> 00:44:15,110
I actually kept telling you about it--

610
00:44:15,111 --> 00:44:17,070
It's too late for that now, isn't it?

611
00:44:17,071 --> 00:44:18,280
Mr. Kim Dupal!

612
00:44:18,281 --> 00:44:20,867
Yes, Mr. Kim Dupal, Mr. Kim Dupal.

613
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:24,244
Mr. Kim Dupal. He-Here it is.

614
00:44:24,245 --> 00:44:28,206
- Oh, thank you. Oh, thank you so much.
- Whoa.

615
00:44:28,207 --> 00:44:30,125
- But this is a bit…
-  This should do.

616
00:44:30,126 --> 00:44:32,961
Just flip it over! No one will notice.

617
00:44:32,962 --> 00:44:36,131
Okay. What are you doing?
Put your gowns on!

618
00:44:36,132 --> 00:44:39,385
- Let's all stay calm now.
-  Uh, Kim Du… Kim Dupal…

619
00:44:46,392 --> 00:44:49,269
How can she be so calm and composed?

620
00:44:49,270 --> 00:44:51,189
Am I the only one losing my mind here?

621
00:44:51,772 --> 00:44:53,899
What is her deal?

622
00:44:58,362 --> 00:44:59,363
Dr. Yong.

623
00:45:00,781 --> 00:45:03,951
I'll leave the mugwort
and the cups in the therapy room.

624
00:45:05,119 --> 00:45:06,495
Okay.

625
00:45:17,298 --> 00:45:18,883
I'm so scared.

626
00:45:28,226 --> 00:45:30,477
She's here, she's here!

627
00:45:36,525 --> 00:45:37,735
Welcome, ma'am!

628
00:45:40,279 --> 00:45:41,656
Hello.

629
00:45:42,657 --> 00:45:44,951
- Is something going on?
-  Hello.

630
00:45:47,620 --> 00:45:50,622
Oh, um, no. What brings you here?

631
00:45:50,623 --> 00:45:56,378
Our baby's been sniffling for a few days,
and her throat is raw.

632
00:45:56,379 --> 00:45:58,505
Can the doctor of Korean medicine
take a look?

633
00:45:58,506 --> 00:46:00,841
Western medicine isn't helping at all.

634
00:46:01,509 --> 00:46:04,136
-  Can you say "Ah" for me?
- Ah.

635
00:46:08,432 --> 00:46:09,934
Hmm.

636
00:46:11,769 --> 00:46:13,687
Oh.

637
00:46:13,688 --> 00:46:15,356
Her throat's a bit swollen.

638
00:46:16,357 --> 00:46:18,400
Were there any other symptoms?

639
00:46:18,401 --> 00:46:20,193
Like breaking out in a cold sweat.

640
00:46:20,194 --> 00:46:22,612
I don't think so.

641
00:46:22,613 --> 00:46:26,116
Medicine works well for colds,
but acupuncture can also help.

642
00:46:26,117 --> 00:46:28,118
- Oh, I see.
- Let's get you better with it.

643
00:46:28,119 --> 00:46:29,786
No, I don't want it!

644
00:46:29,787 --> 00:46:32,622
- It won't hurt at all.
-  He said it's not gonna hurt.

645
00:46:32,623 --> 00:46:35,166
- This is cool to the touch.
-  Hang in there, okay?

646
00:46:35,167 --> 00:46:37,711
It feels nice and refreshing
when you put it on.

647
00:46:37,712 --> 00:46:38,962
That's refreshing, right?

648
00:46:38,963 --> 00:46:40,464
See? Nice and cool, right?

649
00:46:41,340 --> 00:46:43,925
Oh, hold on.

650
00:46:43,926 --> 00:46:46,429
I think there's something here.

651
00:46:47,179 --> 00:46:49,849
It's an ant. Hold still.

652
00:46:51,392 --> 00:46:52,643
Got it.

653
00:46:54,687 --> 00:46:57,605
Ta-da. That didn't hurt at all, did it?

654
00:46:57,606 --> 00:46:59,150
:cue

655
00:47:06,532 --> 00:47:09,034
- Grandma.
-  It's okay.

656
00:47:09,035 --> 00:47:10,744
Does it hurt?

657
00:47:10,745 --> 00:47:12,955
- Oh, dear.
- It's okay.

658
00:47:14,373 --> 00:47:17,208
Why are you crying?
I know it doesn't hurt one bit.

659
00:47:17,209 --> 00:47:20,211
- It does hurt!
- Oh, dear.

660
00:47:20,212 --> 00:47:23,048
Stop lying! If it really hurt,
you would've cried earlier!

661
00:47:24,300 --> 00:47:25,925
Oh, dear.

662
00:47:25,926 --> 00:47:28,011
- Deokhwa, it's okay.
- It hurts!

663
00:47:28,012 --> 00:47:30,055
Come on, why are you crying?

664
00:47:30,056 --> 00:47:32,223
You liar.

665
00:47:32,224 --> 00:47:36,853
I'm barely holding back my tears myself.
Why are you crying?

666
00:47:40,358 --> 00:47:41,359
Dr. Yong.

667
00:47:42,151 --> 00:47:44,278
Come outside. The director is here.

668
00:47:44,862 --> 00:47:46,072
Oh, okay.

669
00:47:48,115 --> 00:47:49,533
Just a second, Deokhwa.

670
00:48:03,047 --> 00:48:04,173
Welcome, ma'am.

671
00:48:13,599 --> 00:48:16,310
I came here today
to issue an official warning.

672
00:48:16,852 --> 00:48:19,063
Does anyone know what you did wrong?

673
00:48:26,987 --> 00:48:28,531
Which one of you is Dr. Do Jiui?

674
00:48:31,075 --> 00:48:33,911
Th-That would be me.

675
00:48:37,998 --> 00:48:40,334
How would you define
a civil servant, Dr. Do?

676
00:48:41,377 --> 00:48:42,460
Excuse me?

677
00:48:42,461 --> 00:48:45,714
How can a civil servant
managing provincial affairs

678
00:48:46,674 --> 00:48:50,219
not even know the name of the person
leading the organization?

679
00:48:51,178 --> 00:48:53,096
That is a dereliction of your duty

680
00:48:53,097 --> 00:48:54,932
and a direct challenge to authority.

681
00:49:00,688 --> 00:49:01,772
Those were the words…

682
00:49:02,440 --> 00:49:04,358
of Governor Ko Changmok.

683
00:49:07,653 --> 00:49:09,612
Personally, I don't agree with him.

684
00:49:09,613 --> 00:49:12,157
How should a doctor know
what the governor's name is?

685
00:49:12,158 --> 00:49:14,910
I've delivered the governor's words.

686
00:49:15,536 --> 00:49:17,955
And you've received them, so that's that.

687
00:49:21,292 --> 00:49:22,960
Right.

688
00:49:23,794 --> 00:49:27,297
Then, since you came all this way,

689
00:49:27,298 --> 00:49:29,924
how would you like to take a look around?

690
00:49:29,925 --> 00:49:31,635
-  Sure.
-  Okay.

691
00:49:33,220 --> 00:49:34,888
Deokhwa, don't run!

692
00:49:36,557 --> 00:49:38,683
Deokhwa!

693
00:49:38,684 --> 00:49:40,643
-  Ow.
-  Deokhwa!

694
00:49:40,644 --> 00:49:42,687
- Deokhwa!
-  Are you okay?

695
00:49:42,688 --> 00:49:45,148
-  Oh, dear.
-  Come here.

696
00:49:45,149 --> 00:49:46,232
Come here, Deokhwa.

697
00:49:46,233 --> 00:49:48,944
-  Are you all right?
- Let me take a look. Excuse me.

698
00:49:49,820 --> 00:49:51,988
Are you okay? I'm sorry.

699
00:49:51,989 --> 00:49:53,240
Oh, my gosh.

700
00:50:25,105 --> 00:50:29,401
The location and depth of the wound
don't suggest any nerve or muscle damage.

701
00:50:29,944 --> 00:50:32,320
But since you fell,
there may be a wrist fracture

702
00:50:32,321 --> 00:50:34,322
or some foreign debris inside,
:cue

703
00:50:34,323 --> 00:50:36,242
so I think it's best to get an X-ray.

704
00:50:37,409 --> 00:50:39,786
Should I just dress the wound,
or suture it?

705
00:50:39,787 --> 00:50:42,872
That's for
the attending physician to decide.

706
00:50:42,873 --> 00:50:44,041
Why are you asking me?

707
00:50:45,543 --> 00:50:46,877
I'll suture it.

708
00:50:51,340 --> 00:50:52,591
Let's have you wear this.

709
00:50:57,763 --> 00:50:59,181
POLYAMIDE SUTURE

710
00:51:39,722 --> 00:51:40,764
Plastic surgeon?

711
00:51:41,390 --> 00:51:42,640
Yes.

712
00:51:42,641 --> 00:51:45,101
Then I'm in luck.

713
00:51:48,606 --> 00:51:53,192
Attention, all residents.

714
00:51:53,193 --> 00:51:57,030
Due to a sudden high seas
and gale warning,

715
00:51:57,031 --> 00:52:00,575
all passenger ferries and ship operations
have been suspended.

716
00:52:00,576 --> 00:52:03,244
Due to a sudden hazardous seas
and gale warning,

717
00:52:03,245 --> 00:52:06,832
all passenger ferries and ship operations
have been suspended.

718
00:52:07,416 --> 00:52:08,916
We can't have the ferries suspended.

719
00:52:08,917 --> 00:52:12,254
That means the director is stuck with us.

720
00:52:16,675 --> 00:52:20,345
Since the ferry's been suspended,
let's go out for a team dinner.

721
00:52:20,346 --> 00:52:21,764
What do you say?

722
00:52:22,431 --> 00:52:24,474
Uh, wow.

723
00:52:34,109 --> 00:52:37,695
I know you're on-call, Dr. Do,
but everyone else is good to drink, right?

724
00:52:37,696 --> 00:52:39,447
-  That's right.
- Right.

725
00:52:39,448 --> 00:52:42,033
- Director, I don't think you should…
- Just one glass.

726
00:52:42,034 --> 00:52:44,952
Okay everyone,
let's all drink plenty but responsibly.

727
00:52:44,953 --> 00:52:46,621
Here's to the Public Health Center!

728
00:52:46,622 --> 00:52:48,247
Cheers!

729
00:52:48,248 --> 00:52:50,500
My, here's the good stuff.

730
00:52:50,501 --> 00:52:52,752
Here's your wild flounder.

731
00:52:52,753 --> 00:52:56,381
- Here you go.
-  The flounder's here.

732
00:52:56,382 --> 00:52:58,549
Does the center have any issues?

733
00:52:58,550 --> 00:53:01,594
So many,
like you wouldn't believe.

734
00:53:01,595 --> 00:53:05,181
They shut down two clinics last year,

735
00:53:05,182 --> 00:53:08,309
so it's absolute chaos
every time the seasons change.

736
00:53:08,310 --> 00:53:12,064
Ms. Yuk, you've had a decent number
of relationships on the mainland, right?

737
00:53:13,399 --> 00:53:15,650
A decent number, I guess.

738
00:53:15,651 --> 00:53:17,403
So I'm curious.

739
00:53:18,112 --> 00:53:22,365
Is it true that folks on the mainland
don't get clingy and stuff

740
00:53:22,366 --> 00:53:24,535
even after a one-night stand?

741
00:53:25,119 --> 00:53:26,120
Huh?

742
00:53:27,413 --> 00:53:30,498
Well, some people are like that,
and others aren't.

743
00:53:30,499 --> 00:53:32,375
It depends on the person.

744
00:53:32,376 --> 00:53:36,088
But aren't most people like that?
That's how it was on TV shows.

745
00:53:36,755 --> 00:53:38,089
Uh, Ms. Eom…

746
00:53:38,090 --> 00:53:39,091
Yes?

747
00:53:42,594 --> 00:53:43,595
It's nothing.

748
00:53:44,596 --> 00:53:46,389
I'm going to step outside for some air.

749
00:53:46,390 --> 00:53:49,475
-  Oh, goodness.
-  Would you like another glass?

750
00:53:49,476 --> 00:53:51,145
Yes, please.

751
00:53:55,524 --> 00:53:57,859
Goodness, that burns.

752
00:53:57,860 --> 00:53:59,319
Yes, yes.

753
00:53:59,820 --> 00:54:00,821
:cue

754
00:54:03,198 --> 00:54:06,577
CLIFFSIDE RAW FISH RESTAURANT

755
00:54:14,543 --> 00:54:15,794
Can we talk?

756
00:54:32,019 --> 00:54:33,102
I made a mistake--

757
00:54:33,103 --> 00:54:34,563
You don't need to apologize.

758
00:54:35,564 --> 00:54:37,274
Those rumors weren't false anyway.

759
00:54:40,736 --> 00:54:43,989
If only dating doctors makes someone
a doctor-hunter gold digger…

760
00:54:45,866 --> 00:54:49,203
then I am a doctor-hunter gold digger
as people say.

761
00:54:49,828 --> 00:54:51,205
What are you…

762
00:54:53,081 --> 00:54:57,668
I practically lived at the hospital,
so the only guys around were doctors.

763
00:54:57,669 --> 00:54:59,505
Naturally, I dated a few.

764
00:55:00,839 --> 00:55:01,924
That's right.

765
00:55:03,550 --> 00:55:05,385
So I am a doctor-hunter gold digger.

766
00:55:11,934 --> 00:55:14,144
But I told you not to worry, didn't I?

767
00:55:15,229 --> 00:55:16,897
I won't get my hooks into you.

768
00:55:19,608 --> 00:55:20,651
Why not?

769
00:55:21,860 --> 00:55:22,945
Huh?

770
00:55:24,321 --> 00:55:25,405
Why wouldn't you?

771
00:55:26,907 --> 00:55:27,908
I'm a doctor too.

772
00:55:38,043 --> 00:55:40,045
Help!

773
00:55:40,963 --> 00:55:42,922
Somebody, help!

774
00:55:42,923 --> 00:55:44,006
-  Huh?
-  Huh?

775
00:55:44,007 --> 00:55:47,553
Wait, hold on. Let me take her.

776
00:55:52,140 --> 00:55:54,058
Huh?
Oh, goodness. What happened?

777
00:55:54,059 --> 00:55:55,185
Let's sit here.

778
00:55:57,187 --> 00:55:59,856
Deokhwa, can you tell me where it hurts?

779
00:56:00,691 --> 00:56:02,233
Just a moment.

780
00:56:02,234 --> 00:56:03,527
Your throat?

781
00:56:12,536 --> 00:56:15,162
Her hoarse, muffled voice

782
00:56:15,163 --> 00:56:17,708
while seated in a tripod position.

783
00:56:18,875 --> 00:56:21,502
Chin lifted and mouth open
to breathe better.

784
00:56:21,503 --> 00:56:23,337
All classic signs of acute epiglottitis.

785
00:56:23,338 --> 00:56:24,880
INFLAMMATION OF EPIGLOTTIS

786
00:56:24,881 --> 00:56:26,757
Children have narrow airways,

787
00:56:26,758 --> 00:56:29,385
so severe respiratory distress
can become fatal

788
00:56:29,386 --> 00:56:33,180
if they aren't rushed
to a hospital immediately.

789
00:56:33,181 --> 00:56:35,099
It's an emergency.
Call a medical boat.

790
00:56:35,100 --> 00:56:37,435
Get ready for an intubation
and come to the port.

791
00:56:37,436 --> 00:56:38,603
Okay.

792
00:56:38,604 --> 00:56:39,771
INSERTION OF TUBE
INTO BODY PASSAGE

793
00:56:40,355 --> 00:56:41,439
I'll go with him.

794
00:56:41,440 --> 00:56:43,066
-  Someone help me.
- Yes, ma'am.

795
00:56:50,490 --> 00:56:52,868
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

796
00:56:56,330 --> 00:56:59,999
DISPENSARY

797
00:57:00,000 --> 00:57:01,793
ADULT - PEDIATRIC
:cue

798
00:57:06,673 --> 00:57:07,674
All set.

799
00:57:21,521 --> 00:57:22,773
Why won't they pick up?

800
00:57:23,649 --> 00:57:24,775
Hurry, hurry!

801
00:57:25,525 --> 00:57:26,860
- Stethoscope.
- Stethoscope.

802
00:57:27,569 --> 00:57:28,987
Turn her for me.

803
00:57:36,995 --> 00:57:39,247
Oh! The chief's boat is coming in.

804
00:57:40,749 --> 00:57:42,249
This way!

805
00:57:42,250 --> 00:57:43,752
Over here, over here!

806
00:57:45,003 --> 00:57:48,339
- You get ready too, Dr. Do.
- Me? No, I can't.

807
00:57:48,340 --> 00:57:49,840
I'm not a pediatrician,

808
00:57:49,841 --> 00:57:52,134
and I've never done this in a real case.

809
00:57:52,135 --> 00:57:54,179
Get a hold of yourself, Dr. Do.

810
00:57:54,971 --> 00:57:56,138
I have a hand injury,

811
00:57:56,139 --> 00:57:58,642
and you're the only doctor
who didn't drink.

812
00:58:06,692 --> 00:58:08,235
PYEONDONGDO FISHING

813
00:58:09,569 --> 00:58:10,986
I heard from the Coast Guard!

814
00:58:10,987 --> 00:58:14,241
Don't worry,
I'm certified for local emergencies!

815
00:58:15,158 --> 00:58:17,868
I'm taking you out to meet their cutter,
so hurry up and jump in!

816
00:58:17,869 --> 00:58:20,454
Grab my hand.

817
00:58:20,455 --> 00:58:22,623
- Hurry and climb on board.
-  My goodness.

818
00:58:22,624 --> 00:58:25,459
-  It's a race against the clock!
- Come on, let's go.

819
00:58:25,460 --> 00:58:26,461
Careful.

820
00:58:27,295 --> 00:58:30,257
It's going to be okay.

821
00:58:33,009 --> 00:58:34,385
It's okay, Deokhwa.

822
00:58:34,386 --> 00:58:36,471
- I'll get a blanket.
-  Dr. Jiui!

823
00:59:08,003 --> 00:59:09,086
Dr. Jiui.

824
00:59:22,851 --> 00:59:24,895
We agreed to go together, remember?

825
00:59:45,457 --> 00:59:47,374
Put on your life jackets
so we can go.

826
00:59:47,375 --> 00:59:49,461
Okay.

827
00:59:51,421 --> 00:59:54,299
:cue

828
01:00:27,249 --> 01:00:28,333
Dr. Do, Deokhwa…

829
01:00:29,000 --> 01:00:30,584
Deokhwa…

830
01:00:30,585 --> 01:00:33,212
Dr. Do, get ready to intubate her.

831
01:00:33,213 --> 01:00:35,257
Deokhwa…

832
01:00:35,882 --> 01:00:38,133
- Deokhwa, wake up.
- Hurry!

833
01:00:38,134 --> 01:00:40,261
-  Oh, Deokhwa…
- Kill the engine!

834
01:00:52,023 --> 01:00:53,859
You have to do it, Dr. Do.

835
01:01:14,337 --> 01:01:17,257
Captain, he's going to die!
Please go faster!

836
01:01:18,592 --> 01:01:20,760
Seonu!

837
01:01:21,595 --> 01:01:22,888
Seonu!

838
01:01:35,817 --> 01:01:38,861
No, no, I can't do this.

839
01:01:38,862 --> 01:01:40,655
She's already showing signs of cyanosis,

840
01:01:41,489 --> 01:01:43,658
which means we will lose her soon.

841
01:01:44,659 --> 01:01:47,913
Legally, you have a justifiable reason
to refuse treatment,

842
01:01:48,580 --> 01:01:51,290
and I can't force your hand
if you absolutely won't do it.

843
01:01:51,291 --> 01:01:53,209
But please save this child.

844
01:01:58,173 --> 01:02:00,216
Dr. Do, I'll help you. Okay?

845
01:02:03,011 --> 01:02:05,972
- Please.
-  Doctor, please save her.

846
01:02:13,396 --> 01:02:14,480
Let's switch places.

847
01:02:14,481 --> 01:02:16,315
- Okay.
-  Deokhwa…

848
01:02:16,316 --> 01:02:18,318
Deokhwa, hang in there a little longer.

849
01:02:24,991 --> 01:02:27,785
It's a cold intubation
on a moving boat, so it won't be easy.

850
01:02:27,786 --> 01:02:29,787
Get a clear view of the airway first.

851
01:02:29,788 --> 01:02:31,872
Intubation isn't something you do by feel.

852
01:02:31,873 --> 01:02:34,668
You have to have visual confirmation
before you proceed.

853
01:02:37,128 --> 01:02:38,671
I can see the epiglottis.

854
01:02:38,672 --> 01:02:41,340
Can you see the vocal cords?

855
01:02:41,341 --> 01:02:42,716
Uh…

856
01:02:42,717 --> 01:02:45,053
If you drop it there,
you'll hit the esophagus.

857
01:02:45,679 --> 01:02:48,639
Use the laryngoscope blade
to directly lift the epiglottis

858
01:02:48,640 --> 01:02:50,892
so the larynx opens up.

859
01:02:53,728 --> 01:02:56,398
Seonu!

860
01:02:56,898 --> 01:02:58,024
Seonu!

861
01:03:02,570 --> 01:03:04,738
Wh-Whoa. You can't just lift it like that.

862
01:03:04,739 --> 01:03:08,617
If you lever it against the teeth,
the blade will snap them right off.

863
01:03:08,618 --> 01:03:10,453
Lift upward and forward.

864
01:03:16,835 --> 01:03:19,878
Laryngeal edema is obstructing
the view of the trachea.

865
01:03:19,879 --> 01:03:21,214
I can't insert the tube.

866
01:03:22,465 --> 01:03:23,590
How about now?

867
01:03:25,176 --> 01:03:27,387
- It's open. Give me the tube.
- Yes, Doctor.
:cue

868
01:03:36,896 --> 01:03:39,399
- The tube's in. Remove the stylet.
- Yes, Doctor.

869
01:03:40,066 --> 01:03:42,443
- Connect the Ambu bag right away.
- Yes, Doctor.

870
01:03:42,444 --> 01:03:44,029
MANUAL RESUSCITATOR

871
01:03:51,619 --> 01:03:52,620
Stethoscope.

872
01:04:07,385 --> 01:04:09,803
Her cyanosis is gone.

873
01:04:09,804 --> 01:04:13,849
That means
her lungs are getting airflow.

874
01:04:13,850 --> 01:04:15,560
Thank you, Doctor.

875
01:04:31,951 --> 01:04:33,369
Dr. Do, are you okay?

876
01:04:35,163 --> 01:04:36,831
Seonu!

877
01:04:37,332 --> 01:04:38,625
Seonu!

878
01:04:44,964 --> 01:04:45,965
Dr. Do!

879
01:04:52,555 --> 01:04:54,682
Seonu!

880
01:04:55,350 --> 01:04:56,351
Seonu!

881
01:05:07,946 --> 01:05:09,656
- Dr. Do!
- Dr. Do Jiui!

882
01:05:11,407 --> 01:05:12,909
What the…

883
01:05:13,451 --> 01:05:15,160
Dr. Do!

884
01:05:18,039 --> 01:05:20,291
Dr. Do!

885
01:05:45,984 --> 01:05:49,904
DON'T WORRY ABOUT THAT

886
01:05:50,405 --> 01:05:53,991
DOCTORS HAVE AN OBLIGATION

887
01:05:53,992 --> 01:05:59,122
TO RESPECT
THEIR PATIENTS' SECRETS

888
01:06:13,428 --> 01:06:16,848
CHECKING THE PLAYBACK
IS ABSOLUTELY ESSENTIAL!

889
01:06:24,939 --> 01:06:27,941
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

890
01:06:27,942 --> 01:06:29,401
Ms. Hari.

891
01:06:29,402 --> 01:06:31,279
What are you hesitating for?

892
01:06:32,780 --> 01:06:34,198
Are you going?

893
01:06:34,199 --> 01:06:35,574
He's way too conscious of her.

894
01:06:35,575 --> 01:06:37,409
So it was you, Ms. Yuk Hari.

895
01:06:37,410 --> 01:06:39,828
I guess the rumors are true.

896
01:06:39,829 --> 01:06:41,706
That Ms. Yuk Hari is a doctor hunter.

897
01:06:42,957 --> 01:06:45,376
That woman…
She's not really into you.

898
01:06:46,252 --> 01:06:48,253
But you said
we should give this a go.

899
01:06:48,254 --> 01:06:49,338
Hari.

900
01:06:49,339 --> 01:06:51,048
I told you I'm not breaking up with you!

901
01:06:51,049 --> 01:06:53,342
Why? Is it because of
that PH doc you came here with?

902
01:06:53,343 --> 01:06:54,552
Dr. Do!

903
01:06:57,931 --> 01:06:59,933
Translated by Yoon Hyuk Park
